.org\/wiki\/Prion_disease\" title=\"Prion disease\" class=\"mw-redirect\">prion disease<\/a> demonstrated to be infectious.<\/p><p>In 1996, Gajdusek was charged with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Child_molestation\" title=\"Child molestation\" class=\"mw-redirect\">child molestation<\/a> and after being convicted, spent 12 months in prison before entering a self-imposed exile in Europe, where he died a decade later.<\/p><p>His papers are held at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Library_of_Medicine\" title=\"National Library of Medicine\" class=\"mw-redirect\">National Library of Medicine<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bethesda,_Maryland\" title=\"Bethesda, Maryland\">Bethesda, Maryland<\/a>. <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Daniel_Carleton_Gajdusek#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Daniel Carleton Gajdusek","place_of_birth":"Yonkers ,  New York ,  U.S.","place_of_death":"Troms\u00f8 ,  Norway","text":"Daniel Carleton Gajdusek , Physiology or Medicine, 1976","year":1976.0}